    "dd1362": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "lang": "lg-nolan",
        "value": "<p>Use this tool to create a thesaurus with different data from different sections, as types or mints to create a tree catalog, ex: types inside mints.</p><p>Define the tool config and assign with the 2 ddo list to view in the right and left.</p><p>for the right panel: define a ddo of the main section with the &nbsp;components to show.</p><p>the role property need to be: \"section_to_cataloging\"</p><p>for the left pane: define the ddo with the area_thesarurs (filtered by hierarche_types or other concept):</p><p>the role property need to be: \"area_thesaurus\",</p><p>{</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"mode\": \"relation\",</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"role\": \"area_thesaurus\",</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"tipo\": \"dd100\",</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"properties\": {</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \"hierarchy_types\": [8]</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; },</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"section_id\": null,</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"section_tipo\": \"dd100\"</p><p>}</p><p></p><p>The catalog tool create new section when the user drag any record from section to the thesaurus and it's necessary define where will be storage the locator drag as:</p><p>\"set_new_thesaurus_value\": {</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"tipo\": \"numisdata656\",</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; \"section_tipo\": \"numisdata665\"</p><p>}</p>"
      }
    ],
